data.meta_description: Highlights features and amenities found at Cypress Point Park.
data.text:
This neighborhood park has beach, trail, sand volleyball court, playground, disc golf course, and shelters. The parking lot is very active and the park is a favorite spot for locals to enjoy lunch breaks or evening sunsets.

Address:

5620 W Cypress St

Tampa, FL 33607

Park Hours:

Sunrise to sunset

Phone Numbers:

(813) 274-8615 - Park Administration

(813) 274-8184 - Shelter Reservations

Beach

The calm and tranquil white sand beach of Cypress Point offers breathtaking views of Tampa Bay with occasional flyovers from planes landing at Tampa International Airport. This is also a popular spot to catch a Florida stunning sunset.

Disc Golf Course

A disc golf course that will challenge even the most enthusiastic players. Concrete tee pads, good signage, places to sit, and not much other activity on the grounds, all add to the experience. Some of the courses may have standing water so wear appropriate foot gear. A creek comes into play on two holes.

Playground

The playground is centralized to the active area located close to the restrooms and shelters. It features areas to climb, hop, and test the balance. Benches face the playground to watch your child play in the Florida sun.

Sand Volleyball Court

There is one sand volleyball court located east of the parking lot.

Shelters

Spacious shelters are available for your outdoor event and are equipped with picnic tables, grills and trash receptacles. Permitting for the shelters is handled by the shelter office.

Request a Shelter

Trails

Shaded trails wind through the length of the park offering views of nature and wildlife. One trail is paved and the other is unpaved and connected at various points along the trails.

PADL Standup Paddleboards

This is a self-service rental station for stand-up paddle boards. Rates are by the hour and memberships are available.

Rent A Paddleboard
